Just noticed that this could probably be restructured slightly:
```C#
if (successfulSend)
{
    errorCode = SocketError.Success;
    return false;
}
else if (errno == Interop.Error.EAGAIN)
{
    errorCode = SocketError.WouldBlock;
    return false;
}
else
{
    errorCode = GetSocketErrorForErrorCode(errno);
    return true;
}
```
Note that EAGAIN has the same value as EWOULDBLOCK, so I don't think we need to do the comparison twice.

